Publication date: December 14, 2025

Free access to the "Lyrica" mobile app functionality

1. General provisions
1.1. This document constitutes an official offer (a public offer) made by Igor Andreevich Vasserman, a self-employed individual of the Russian Federation, TIN 550145206811 (hereinafter — the "Provider"), addressed to any individual (hereinafter — the "User"), to provide free access to the functionality of the Lyrica mobile app (hereinafter — the "App") on the terms set out below.

1.2. This document is a public offer under Articles 435 and 437(2) of the Civil Code of the Russian Federation.

1.3. Acceptance of this offer (full and unconditional acceptance of its terms) is the User using the App, including registering an account and using the App's functionality.

1.4. Acceptance of the offer means the conclusion of an agreement on the terms of this offer. The agreement is deemed concluded from the moment the User starts using the App.

2. Subject of the agreement
2.1. The Provider grants the User free access to the functionality of the Lyrica mobile app, including all available features and capabilities of the App.

2.2. The services are provided remotely in electronic (digital) form. No physical goods are delivered.

2.3. The App is provided free of charge. All App features are available to the User without restrictions and without payment.

3. App features
3.1. The Lyrica App includes the following features:
– Cloud storage for lyrics: synchronization and storage of lyrics across the User's devices.
– Cloud storage for quick notes: instant synchronization of notes between devices.
– Internal rhymes: enhanced analysis and highlighting of internal rhymes in lyrics.
– Detailed rhymes: enhanced rhyme analysis taking stresses and consonance into account.
– And other features available in the App.

3.2. The current list of features is displayed in the App and may be updated by the Provider.

3.3. All App features are provided free of charge and without restrictions.

4. Access provision
4.1. Access to App features is provided automatically after registering an account in the App.

4.2. The service is deemed to start when the User is granted access to App features.

4.3. In case of technical issues, the User may contact support: iva28app@gmail.com.

4.4. Cloud data retention
4.4.1. If the User used cloud synchronization/storage features, the User's content may be stored in cloud infrastructure to provide the service.
4.4.2. The User may delete cloud data at any time using the App's functionality (if available) or by contacting support.
4.4.3. Data deletion applies to cloud content and does not affect local data stored on the User's device.

5. Rights and obligations of the parties
5.1. The Provider undertakes to:
– provide access to App features after account registration;
– maintain the App's operability within reasonable limits.

5.2. The User undertakes to:
– provide accurate information during registration;
– not use the App for unlawful purposes; and
– not take actions that disrupt the App's operation.

6. Limitation of liability
6.1. The App is provided "as is". The Provider makes reasonable efforts to ensure stable operation but does not guarantee uninterrupted operation due to circumstances beyond the Provider's control.

6.2. The Provider is not liable for:
– failures of internet providers or app stores;
– the User's device malfunctions; or
– actions of third parties.

6.3. The Provider is not liable for any damage caused to the User as a result of using or inability to use the App.

7. Personal data
7.1. By using the App, the User confirms that they have read and agree with the Privacy Policy.

7.2. The User consents to the processing of personal data in accordance with Federal Law No. 152‑FZ "On Personal Data" for the purpose of performing this agreement.

8. Governing law and dispute resolution
8.1. This agreement is governed by the laws of the Russian Federation, including the Civil Code and the Law of the Russian Federation No. 2300‑1 "On Protection of Consumer Rights".

8.2. Disputes are resolved through negotiations. If no agreement is reached, the dispute is referred to the court at the Provider's location or, at the User's choice, at the User's place of residence.

9. Provider status
9.1. The Provider applies the special tax regime "Tax on Professional Income" (self‑employed) under Federal Law No. 422‑FZ of November 27, 2018.

10. Final provisions
10.1. The Provider may amend the terms of this offer. Amendments take effect from the moment the new version is published, unless otherwise stated.

10.2. Continued use of the App after publication of amendments constitutes the User's acceptance of the new version.

10.3. This offer is valid indefinitely until withdrawn by the Provider.

10.4. The Provider may at any time change the terms of access to the App, including the possibility of introducing paid features or restrictions, by notifying Users through the App or by other means.

